<br>
If you're of the view that imprisonment is a way of punishing people for their crimes, then it's illogical to argue that prison should be used at all.  If you want to punish someone for a serious crime, it makes a lot more sense to inflict physical harm on them.<br>
<br>
For example, if you're of the &quot;punishment&quot; mentality, then logically the way to treat a rapist isn't to stick him in prison.  It makes a lot more sense to have him flogged or beaten, and possibly (for repeat offenders) surgically altered so he wasn't physically capable of repeating his crime.<br>
<br>
In the case of even more serious crimes, like murder or very serious bodily harm, you can ensure that the criminal will never, ever repeat his offences by performing an operation called a prefrontal lobotomy.  After being lobotomized, the former criminal can be given simple tasks to perform for the benefit of society, which would hopefully help to cover the cost of the punishment.<br>
<br>
If you're of the &quot;protection&quot; mentality, you take the view that the prisoner is someone who has forfeited the trust of the society.  For its own protection, the society puts the prisoner in a place where he cannot possibly do it any further harm.  However, since the purpose of prison isn't to punish but to protect, the society takes reasonable steps to ensure that the prisoner's period of incarceration is - if not pleasant - at least not actively unpleasant, and that the prisoner is treated with what the society feels is &quot;normal human decency.&quot;<br>
<br>
Most Western states are on the &quot;protection&quot; side of the fence.  Prisoners are well-treated, and punishments such as floggings and amputations are not performed; the view is that the prisoner has extensive rights, and the only right which has been taken away from him is the right to venture out into society.<br>
<br>
Many non-Western states are on the &quot;punishment&quot; side.  Prisons are awful hellholes, and floggings, beatings, and amputations are performed as part of the normal court justice system.<br>
<br>
I think a lot of people in this thread are taking the view that prison should be both protection and punishment, but to me, that's illogical.  If you're going to start to punish people for their crimes rather than just protect society, there are a lot better ways of doing it rather than imprisonment... surgical alterations, while not cheap, would certainly be both cheaper and more effective than prison. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=162740">Shadowfrost</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mysidiadrakkenbane>MysidiaDrakkenbane</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/extern/724222.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bitch with the Ban Stick</span><br>  Posts: 2239<br> <font color=#330000>(10/3/03 7:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=19>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/1829785.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How the hell is this an invasion of privacy?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Many non-Western states are on the &quot;punishment&quot; side. Prisons are awful hellholes, and floggings, beatings, and amputations are performed as part of the normal court justice system.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
